<row bottom="minor"><cell></cell><cell></cell></row>
<row><cell><m>-2</m></cell><cell><m>-0.65</m></cell></row>
<row><cell><m>-\sqrt{\pi}</m></cell><cell><m>-1</m></cell></row>
<row><cell>0</cell><cell>1</cell></row>
<row><cell><m>\sqrt{\pi}</m></cell><cell><m>-1</m></cell></row>
<row><cell>2</cell><cell><m>-0.65</m></cell></row>
</tabular>
</table>
<p>
From the table it is clear that the maximum value of <m>f</m> on <m>[-2,2]</m> is 1; the minimum value is <m>-1</m>. The graph in <xref ref="fig_extval6">Figure</xref> confirms our results.
</p>
