<subsection>
<title>Review</title>
<exercise>
<statement>
<p>
Find <m>\frac{dy}{dx}</m>, where <m>x^2y-y^2x = 1</m>.
</p>
</statement>
<answer>
<p>
<m>\frac{dy}{dx} = \frac{y (y-2 x)}{x (x-2 y)}</m>
</p>
</answer>
</exercise>

<exercise>
<statement>
<p>
Find the equation of the line tangent to the graph of <m>x^2+y^2+xy=7</m> at the point <m>(1,2)</m>.
</p>
</statement>
<answer>
<p>
<m>y=-4/5(x-1)+2</m>
</p>
</answer>
</exercise>

<exercise>
<statement>
<p>
Let <m>f(x) = x^3+x</m>.
</p>

<p>
Evaluate <m>\ds \lim_{s\to 0} \frac{f(x+s)-f(x)}{s}</m>.
</p>
</statement>
<answer>
<p>
<m>3x^2+1</m>
</p>
</answer>
</exercise>
